06/06/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- EU Enlargement Commissioner Olli Rehn has told Macedonian Prime Minister Vlado Buckovski that the enlargement process would continue and that the European Commission is preparing its position regarding Skopje's application for official candidate member status. 
The two met Sunday (5 June) during a working visit Buckovski made to Finland.
In other news, Macedonian police found an illegal arms depot Friday in the village of Tanusevci, at the Macedonian-Kosovo border. 
The area was an ethnic Albanian rebel stronghold during the 2001 interethnic conflict. 
(Macedonian Government Web site - 06/06/05; A1 TV - 05/06/05; A1 TV, Telma TV - 03/06/05)
